xyz.swatt.data_mapping

Class LocalDateTimeMapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.swatt.data_mapping.LocalDateTimeMapping
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataMapping

    @LogMethods
public class LocalDateTimeMapping
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataMapping

    Use this class to validate that 2 different LocalDateTimes, LocalDates, LocalTimes, ZonedDateTimes, or Strings Representing Date and/or Time are equal.

    Other Date and Time Classes Supported: TemporalAccessor ( LocalDate ).

    Note: Because of the large number of supported class, you must use setSource(...) and setDestination(...) methods, on top of the constructor.

    Warning: Be careful when comparing (Date)Times both with and without Time Zones. (Date)Times without Time Zones will be treated as having come from the Local (System Default) Time Zone.

    Note: This class is used instead of direct comparison, to simplify large batches of comparisons, and to provide common functionality.

    Author:
    Brandon Dudek (BrandonDudek)
